    "Content": "<h1 id=\"joseph-mercola\">Joseph Mercola</h1>\n<p>Joseph Mercola -- an alternative medicine huckster -- is promoted in <em>RiverEast</em> letters as a valuable source of information on subjects like Covid vaccines.</p>\n<p>He is slicker than many of these snake-oil salesmen.  But he has no more reasonable arguments than any of them.</p>\n<p>As is often the case, a <a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?q=joseph+mercola\">simple web search</a> is a good place to start.  This should lead you to many sites, including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Mercola\">Wikipedia</a> and to sites noting his top place among the <a href=\"https://www.counterhate.com/disinformationdozen\">Disinformation Dozen</a>, and include links to the New York Times <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/24/technology/joseph-mercola-coronavirus-misinformation-online.html\">article</a> <em>The Most Influential Spreader of Coronavirus Misinformation Online</em>.  (This is behind a paywall, but through October 31, 2021 there is a <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/24/technology/joseph-mercola-coronavirus-misinformation-online.html?unlocked_article_code=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACEIPuonUktbfqohkT1UZBybJUNMnqBqCgvfeh747nXLmLG2QRCxJyOAcRoOH4UDLbLRifcYomjGaX95HPrg1QfVuz-hZektrTwiur92EhJEBaW0TmL6EY1kXjdjLTKxqtnjjdHW4I-Nyg7O0sx_daDHqRPPb0H0-IAxm9o81cQuhxX1fwPqRFuYm2YZ42OwzRcwvHUd2byaKvvntCxRsap7RPlyHtF5AC6wOUirTnNWf97oCbA1XbFrMR3t66m82g8hObJJVZO2sak59J7etxOkZGWdqL4-2B5QuRYCyl7RisbDFqB3k29PaffVAbPthtqInQR3j601i&amp;smid=url-share\">freely shared</a> version you can read.)</p>\n"
